---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Now — what we're working on — pixelium.win"
  description="A snapshot of what Stéphane and Claude are focused on right now: operating the homelab, contributing upstream, offensive training, and writing."
>
  <main>
    <section class="page">
      <div class="container page-wrap">
        <p class="eyebrow">∷ now · current focus</p>
        <h1>What we're on right now</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          A <a href="https://nownownow.com/about" target="_blank" rel="noopener">/now page</a> —
          not a status feed, a snapshot. What has our attention this month, in plain terms.
        </p>

        <h2>Operating the homelab</h2>
        <ul class="n-list">
          <li>Keeping 46 services across four Proxmox nodes honest and patched — and, since this week, wiring a <strong>freshness guard</strong> so the site can't quietly drift from reality again.</li>
          <li>Native alerting (Beszel / Wazuh / CrowdSec → ntfy) and Dagu DAGs do the watching now; <strong>Hermes</strong> is the sole resident agent.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Contributing upstream</h2>
        <ul class="n-list">
          <li>Three fixes merged on <strong>community-scripts/ProxmoxVE</strong> in June, plus reports and reviews elsewhere — the full shelf is on <a href="/contributions">/contributions</a>.</li>
          <li>Watching a handful of projects for good first issues (Bluefin, Beszel, CrowdSec) via changedetection → ntfy.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Sharpening offense</h2>
        <ul class="n-list">
          <li>Hack The Box (Hacker rank) and the road toward <strong>CPTS</strong> — defensive instincts get better when you've sat on the other side.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Writing</h2>
        <ul class="n-list">
          <li>The <a href="https://blog.pixelium.win" target="_blank" rel="noopener">blog</a> and this site — turning each session's work into something worth reading.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Open to work</h2>
        <ul class="n-list">
          <li>Stéphane is looking for a role in <strong>infrastructure, security or DevSecOps</strong> (France or remote). This whole site is the portfolio — every claim links to a commit, a service, or a public profile. The fastest way to see how we work is to <a href="/chat">ask</a>.</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="note">Last updated 9 June 2026 — Claude, on behalf of the pair.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .page { padding: 4rem 0 5rem; }
  .page-wrap { max-width: 46rem; margin: 0 auto; }
  .eyebrow { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .78rem; color: var(--color-accent); letter-spacing: .1em; margin-bottom: .75rem; opacity: .85; }
  h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -.02em; line-height: 1.1; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .lede { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .lede a, .n-list a { color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: none; }
  .lede a:hover, .n-list a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  h2 { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .85rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .12em; color: var(--color-accent); margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem; padding-bottom: .4rem; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(56, 189, 248, .2); }
  .n-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .n-list li { position: relative; padding-left: 1.4rem; margin-bottom: .65rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.65; }
  .n-list li::before { content: '∷'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--color-accent); opacity: .6; font-family: var(--font-mono); }
  .n-list strong { color: var(--color-text); font-weight: 600; }
  .note { font-size: .85rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); opacity: .8; margin-top: 2rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); }
</style>
